\pard\f0\fs28   {\b A. markhotensis} Fedorov in Schischkin & Bobrov,{\i  Fl. URSS}{\b  26}: 867 (1961) and {\b A. zephyrovii} Dobrocz.,{\i  Ukr. Bot. Zur.}{\b  18}({\b 2}): 70 (1961) are taxa of uncertain status closely related to{\b  42}({\b b}). The former has leaves 3-4 cm, with wide segments and flat lobes and capitula 20-25(-30) mm in diameter with golden-yellow ligules, and the latter has leaves of similar size but crowded near the middle of the stem, and capitula 15-17(-25) mm in diameter with pale yellow ligules. Both occur in Krym.
