\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 45. A. cretacea} Zefirov, {\i Not. Syst.} ({\i Leningrad}) {\b 16}: 371 (1954). Greyish- or whitish-lanate perennial. Stems 10-25 cm, decumbent, numerous, simple or branched. Leaves up to 3·5 cm, oblong, pinnatisect; segments oblong, pectinate-dentate, somewhat distant; teeth mucronate. Capitula 12-20(-25) mm in diameter; peduncles 2-8 cm. Involucre hemispherical-subcampanulate, whitish-lanate; bracts rigid and rather thick at base, the outer lanceolate, very acute, without a scarious margin, the inner ovate-oblong to oblong with obtuse or subobtuse hyaline apex, narrowly edged with pale brown, fimbriate. Ligules 4-7 × 2·25 mm, bright yellow. Disc 7-13 mm in diameter, deeper yellow than ligules. Receptacle subhemispherical; scales about equalling the florets. Corona c. ¼ as long as achene. {\i Stony calcareous slopes. S.W. Krym.} Rs (K). ({\i Caucasus}.)
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   {\b A. parviceps} Dobrocz. & Fedorov in Zerov et al., {\i Vyzn. Rosl. Ukr. }676 (1965), from Krym, is like {\b 45} but has erect or ascending stems 25-50 cm and pale yellow ligules. Its taxonomic rank is uncertain.
