\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 46. A. monantha} Willd., {\i Sp. Pl.} 3: 2187 (1803). Green perennial with very sparse indumentum. Stems 25-40 cm, usually solitary, simple or with few branches at base, leafy below the middle. Leaves 1-4 × 0·5-1·5 cm, oblong-ovate, with flat segments. Capitula 25-30 mm in diameter. Ligules pale yellow. 2n = 18.{\i  Grassy or stony slopes and roadsides. • Mountains of Krym.} Rs (K).
